Greetings from Montreal.

My name is Jim McDannald and I’m the founder of <https://podiatrygrowth.com|Podiatry Growth> which provides digital marketing services to podiatrists.

I was a surgical podiatrist in the US before switching careers and went on to work in writing/marketing roles with <http://Wirecutter.com|Wirecutter.com>, <http://Polar.com|Polar.com> and the Canadian Olympic track and field team.

I’m looking forward to improving my content marketing chops and contributing to this community.

text:
Hey folks! Really excited to be part of this place.

I’ve got a few irons in the fire currently:

• I’m a content creator focused on marketing, entrepreneurism, digital nomads, and customer support, and I’ve also got some side projects brewing related to travel photography and history! Just call me a “Jake-of-all-trades” :smile: 
• I’m a content creation/marketing freelancer, and also offer services as a customer support consultant 
• Aaaaaand I’m also employed by Toggl, the time tracker app as a support specialist. 
I came across Superpath through a tweet and couldn’t believe my luck in finding this community. I thought that content marketing folks were islands unto themselves, and am really grateful to be a part of this. Hope to share some of my knowledge and learn a lot from all you amazing people here!
